## 4. docker-compose.windows.yml — Windows Docker Desktop

Differences from the default:

- No `network_mode: host` (unsupported on Docker Desktop for Windows)
- Explicit `127.0.0.1:9119:9119` port mapping for the dashboard
- `${USERPROFILE}/.hermes` Windows-style volume path
- Pulls `nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest` from a registry (no local build)
- Uses `--insecure` to bind the dashboard to `0.0.0.0` inside the container
  (the published port is still localhost-only on the host)

Run with:

```
docker compose -f docker-compose.windows.yml up -d
```

