## 8. Branding state (as of 2026-06-15)

The container assets still carry Hermes / Nous Research naming throughout.
Tiered by how risky it is to rename:

### Cosmetic-only — safe to rebrand now

- `docker-compose.yml`: `image: hermes-agent`, `container_name: hermes` /
  `hermes-dashboard`, header comment
- `docker-compose.windows.yml`: `image: nousresearch/hermes-agent:latest`
  (← external-facing registry leak), `container_name`, header comment

### Deep coupling — deferred (~2,600 refs)

These propagate through `stage2-hook.sh`, `main-wrapper.sh`,
`hermes-exec-shim.sh`, the cont-init scripts, `hermes_cli/build_info.py`,
`tools/lazy_deps.py`, supervised s6 services, the legacy `/usr/bin/tini`
shim (#34192), and external orchestration templates (Hostinger catalog):

- `/opt/hermes` install root
- `HERMES_HOME`, `HERMES_UID`, `HERMES_GID`, `HERMES_WEB_DIST`,
  `HERMES_TUI_DIR`, `HERMES_GIT_SHA`, `HERMES_DOCKER_EXEC_AS_ROOT`
- `hermes` Linux user (UID 10000)
- `/opt/hermes/.hermes_build_sha`
- Image internal script names (`hermes-exec-shim.sh`, etc.)

A future rename pass should treat these as one atomic migration, not a
piecemeal edit.

