## 9. Troubleshooting

| Symptom                                              | Likely cause / fix                                                                                  |
| ---------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `tini: No such file or directory`                    | External wrapper pinned to `/usr/bin/tini`; the symlink shim at line 86 of the Dockerfile fixes it. |
| Dashboard unreachable on Windows                     | You're on the default compose file; use `-f docker-compose.windows.yml`.                            |
| Files in `~/.hermes` owned by UID 10000              | `HERMES_UID` / `HERMES_GID` not exported before `docker compose up`.                                |
| Chat tab dies with `[session ended]` / 502           | `HERMES_TUI_DIR` not pointing at the prebuilt bundle — see Dockerfile comment near line 270.        |
| `hermes dump` reports `(unknown)` upstream sha       | Image built without `--build-arg HERMES_GIT_SHA=...`; CI sets this automatically.                   |
| `ModuleNotFoundError: hindsight_client` after update | Hindsight client lost on image update — already baked in current Dockerfile (line 165 comment).     |
| `EACCES` on `uv pip install` from lazy_deps          | `.venv` ownership broken; the `chown -R hermes:hermes /opt/hermes/.venv` step at line 208 fixes it. |
